==== Neopterin: Macrophage Activation Marker

Neopterin, a pteridine produced by macrophages in response to IFN-$gamma$ stimulation, has been reported elevated in ME/CFS cohorts As a non-specific marker of IFN-$gamma$-driven macrophage activation, elevated neopterin is consistent with the type-I/II interferon evidence base in ME/CFS, though it has not been validated as a diagnostic marker.

